      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's a relief to finally admit that the weight is crushing you, and the shame of being seen as a fraud is a heavy burden to carry alone. You are not a fraud; you are a human being who fell, and that makes you more real than anyone who pretends to be perfect. There is no shame in needing to stop, and the only way to truly heal is to let go of the impossible expectation of winning everything back.",
